Information for JH & JV Volleyball & Football --

Monday, September 14 @ Callaway

Volleyball:

post_text: Hey Everyone...we are so EXCITED for the 2020-2021 school year at Anselmo-Merna Public School! We sure have missed the students! Some new procedures and policies are in place to help keep the students and staff healthy, happy, and here. We have developed and implemented new classroom and school expectations for the new school year. This entails being: SAFE, RESPECTFUL, and ACCOUNTABLE. We have these posters hanging in the hallways, by the bathrooms, in the classrooms, and various places in the school to make all students aware of the expectations. We will continue to implement more positive behavior expectations and protocols in our school throughout the year! Good luck and enjoy the new school year students, parents, and staff!

Name: Tina Marie Baxter

post_text:
Quickly approaching deadline to apply for National Honor Society!

Attention current 10th & 11th grade students interested in National Honor Society--

* To be eligible to become a member for the National Honor Society a candidate must be a sophomore or junior who has an 89.0% average. The candidate then must complete an application that explains how he or she will uphold the principals of the National Honor Society. Each candidate is evaluated by the high school faculty, who use as a criteria the principles of the National Honor Society. As required by the National Honor Society Constitution, each candidate is then reviewed and voted upon by a five member faculty council appointed annually by the principal. A majority vote by the faculty council required to become a National Honor Society member.

Notice -- Sports Physicals

Due to the Coronavirus:

Sports physicals on file for the 2019-2020 school year for any current 9-11 grade students will now be valid for the 2020-2021 school year. All incoming freshmen (current 8th graders) will still be required to provide sports physical paperwork that is dated no earlier than May 1, 2020.

The physicals that the current 7th graders have on file for the 2019-2020 school year can be used for NSAA/athletic purposes for the 2020-2021 school year. Incoming 7th graders (current 6th graders) will still need a physical & vaccinations.

post_text:
Attention current 10th & 11th grade students interested in National Honor Society--

* To be eligible to become a member for the National Honor Society a candidate must be a sophomore or junior who has an 89.0% average. The candidate then must complete an application that explains how he or she will uphold the principals of the National Honor Society. Each candidate is evaluated by the high school faculty, who use as a criteria the principles of the National Honor Society. As required by the National Honor Society Constitution, each candidate is then reviewed and voted upon by a five member faculty council appointed annually by the principal. A majority vote by the faculty council required to become a National Honor Society member.

post_text:
School is temporarily closed, but feeding our students is still a priority. Please read on for information regarding free lunch/breakfasts for our district kids.

The school will be providing a free lunch each day ready to pick up from 12-1 in the school cafeteria & also at the community building in Anselmo. When you grab lunch for that day, you will also be able to grab a bag for breakfast the next morning. This service will be available M-F while the school is closed beginning tomorrow, Wednesday, March 18. Anyone from 0 to 18 years old and have at least one sibling enrolled in our school are welcome and urged to take advantage of these school provided lunches.

There are also some families that are enrolled in the backpack program. We would like to extent the backpack program to more than the current families. If you would like to start receiving a backpack, please fill out the attached forms. Backpacks can be picked up on Fridays when lunch is picked up as usual.

As always, if you have any questions, please contact the school.

post_text: The Youth Leadership Custer County is an organization which promotes initiative among high school students within the Custer County area. Each school has a team that is tasked with creating a project designed to better the community. The Anselmo Merna YLCC team has decided to dedicate a memorial bench in memory of Logan Maring, a 2019 graduate of A-M. At the Friday, February 14 basketball game against Ansley/Litchfield they are hosting a split the pot raffle to help fund the installment of this bench, which will be located in downtown Merna. Tickets cost $1 each or 6 for $5 and can be purchased at the concession stand. All proceeds of this fundraiser will go towards funding the memorial. The winner will be announced at halftime of the boys game. Thank you!

post_text:
Today was a special day in Coyote Country. To kick off Homecoming week, our administration was able to grill for our students. Our students were served the finest beef in the United States, Custer County beef. We are so thankful for the constant support from our communities of Anselmo and Merna. A special thank you to Tom and Lisa McMillan for their donation of 600 pounds of locally raised beef that will be fed directly to our students. Also, thank you to Gary Geiselman for his generous donation for processing costs. Our students and staff are are always reminded why it is a great day to be a Coyote. Thank you, parents and community members, for making Anselmo-Merna a great place to learn and live. We are blessed.
If you are interested in donating to the A-M Beef in School program, please contact Logan Lightfoot at the school or Logan.lightfoot@amcoyotes.org

post_text:
Coyote Trivia Time!

Want to score some free food or great Coyote SWAG? Three simple steps:
1. Show up to Thursday's football game
2. Figure out the answer to one of the questions below
3. Find Dr. Lightfoot or Mr. Wells, and tell them the answer.

***A correct answer will score you either free concession stand items, or a slick "It's a Great Day to Be a Coyote" T-shirt!

1. Anselmo-Merna HS is currently tied at #1 all time in the state of Nebraska (all classes) for 1,000 yard rushers. How many total 1,000 yard rushers have we had at A-M?
2. A-M serves two wonderful communities, and the school is located in Merna. How did the Village of Merna get its name? Hint: major female influence on this one!
